<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-543-367  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 543 367.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC User  Sept 26 1990 n142 p24(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EMAP Business andamp; Computer Publications(England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM boosts mainframes with Enterprise range. (Enterprise System9000) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Product:   IBM Enterprise System/9000 (Mainframe computer) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionMainframe Computers.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>IBM boosts mainframes with Enterprise range IBM has announced a new family ofmainframes called the Enterprise System/9000 (ES/9000), including a top ofthe range machine which is almost twice as powerful as any computer it haslaunched before.andP;  Prices range from around $70,500 for an entry-level machineto $22.8 million for the top-end water-cooled Model 900.andM;The fact that IBM described the launch as its most important for 25 yearsshows the continuing importance the company places on its mainframe business,which accounts for around 17 per cent of its sales but nearly half of itsprofits.andM;However, its existing mainframe range has come under increasing pressure,primarily from Japanese competitors Fujitsu and Hitachi and from US-basedAmdahl, all of whom make IBM-compatible mainframes.andM;According to US analysts, the Gartner Group, IBM's share of the world'smainframe market has slipped and could be down to 70 per cent by 1993.andM;IBM's launch follows new mainframe lines from Fujitsu, NEC and Hitachi, andIBM's new mainframes are still not as powerful as the top Fujitsu machines.andM;However, IBM has emphasised other improvements, such as the ES/9000's betterdata security, connectivity and ease of use.andP;  It has also emphasised the roleof the mainframe as a server within a distributed client/server computingmodel as well as in its traditional role.andM;The ES/9000s can be connected using high-speed fibre optic cables which, aswell as providing better security, permit clusters of machines to beconnected over long distances.andM;IBM also announced new minicomputers in its System 390 family as replacementsfor its 4381 and 9370 machines.andM;In addition, it has added two lowcost models to its AS/400 range ofdepartmental minicomputers bringing the entry-level price down by 29 per centto 9,885 pounds.andO;</TEXT></DOC>